##Dictation | 3 people in a family of 6 are suffering from new pneumonia after a hard winter

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

These days, my life is in a mess, I am worried about this or that, three relatives separated, I am alone with two children, could be a leisurely time at home, but because of the epidemic let my family difficult.

Dictation | leaf (alias)

Arrangement | Huang Qi

Today is my 33rd birthday -- Foshan 20200220, it looks like a good number, but I'm going crazy.

The Neighborhood Committee called me this morning and asked me to take my two children to the central quarantine point because three of my family of six had been previously diagnosed with new pneumonia. Now my parents and husband are in the Shelter Hospital and the central isolation point, my children and I are the "survivors" of my family.

We don't have any symptoms, and my mom was the last one to leave the house, and she's been gone for 12 days. We haven't had contact with a patient in 12 days, and I don't think we're infected.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The foliage family

I want to continue to quarantine at home, my two children a 3-year-old and 6-year-old, normal resistance is not good, I fear to concentrate on the quarantine point, but infected by others. I told the neighborhood committee about my family situation, but they said that according to current regulations, we have to go.

Yesterday I imagined making a cake for myself at home today, spending this special birthday with my two daughters, and video chatting with my parents and husband. I even had a birthday wish: "I hope my family are healthy and safe! ! "

Right now, I'm cleaning, I'm packing..

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Leaf, take the two kids to the quarantine point

The community kind of took care of us and connected with a car to take us a big two small to the quarantine point, otherwise we would have to take the bus.

Husband has a fever, mother has a cough, father has a fever

The first person in my family to have a fever was my husband.

Two days before New Year's Eve, my husband was on vacation at work. We spent almost all of the vacation together, so we still don't know how he got infected.

On New Year's Eve, our small family had a New Year's dinner at home. In the evening, the children also watched the Spring Festival evening party. Until then, we thought the virus was a long way off, since we lived in Wuchang, across the river from Hankou.

On the morning of January 26, my husband suddenly had a fever. He had no other symptoms, including dizziness and weakness, and his fever was not high, less than 38 degrees. At that time, I was still quite worried. I made him wear a mask and eat the traditional Chinese medicine that was always kept at home, for colds and regulating the spleen and stomach. The next day, my husband's fever broke. On the night of January 29, my husband started to have a fever of 37.7 degrees again. He said he might be a little cold after taking a bath. That night we put him in isolation, leaving him alone in the bedroom, the older daughter in the study in a small bed, I and the younger daughter's parents crowded in the next bed. January 30th, husband's fever peaked at 102. From January 29 to February 2, her husband has been repeatedly low-grade fever, no cough, the state of basic normal, good spirit, rice is normal to eat, said to eat taste.

At that time, the rule in Wuhan was to keep everyone isolated at home, because the husband's symptoms were not serious and it was already known that going to the hospital was also dangerous, so we decided to continue isolation at home.

The second person who might have been symptomatic was my mother.

On the third day of January 27, my mother went to the supermarket and bought some melon seeds. She was choking when she ate them. Since that day, my mother has occasionally coughed because she had had bronchitis before. At that time, she thought it was bronchitis, too, i took my medication for bronchitis.

The next few days my mom wasn't in the best of spirits. I don't know if I was worried. She was mostly alone in her room and didn't come out much. My Dad cooked with a mask on, and we all wore masks. I still wear a mask every day. I don't even sleep with it off. Looking back now, my mother was not feeling well for a few days, I also have a head stuffy state, my father also said boring, thought that is every day wearing a mask at home.

The other night when I went to bed, I felt a sharp pain in my chest, and I felt chilly. I had to sleep with more cover to feel comfortable, but I would suddenly wake up in the middle of the night because of the sweat on my head. Now that I think about it, maybe the virus was already starting to replicate, and then I started filling myself with Chinese medicine, and about three days later, the chest tingling and sweating disappeared.

Luckily, I wear a mask when I sleep, so that my little girl who has been sleeping with me doesn't have a problem.

On February 2, my husband had a low-grade fever of 37.3 every afternoon. My father also had a sudden fever of 38.5. Dad had been hospitalized for more than a month because of high fever, did not find the cause of illness, so every time dad has a fever we are particularly worried.

Went into quarantine as a "possible patient. "

On the night of February 2, my husband and my parents went to Tianyou Hospital of Wuhan University of Science and Technology, hoping to do a nucleic acid test to confirm. They didn't get back from the hospital until a little after 2:00 a.m. , there were no test kits, no nucleic acid tests. My father and my husband both had blood tests and CT scans, and both of his lungs were infected, but the blood tests weren't too severe; my father had an infection in his right lower lung. According to the diagnostic criteria, they were both neopneumonia, but at the time they had to test positive for nucleic acid, and dad and husband were only suspected patients.

We want to be in a hospital or in a quarantine facility. I called the community, the street, and the Hongshan district at various numbers overnight, and their response was: centralized quarantine only when diagnosed, home quarantine for suspected patients.

But I've got two kids at home, and it's hard for them to stay in their room. And my parents live in the same room, so I can't have a separate room. I was really devastated.

Mother to the hospital also asked the doctor to do a CT examination, but the doctor said it was nothing but a cough, Mother did not do any tests that day on the back.

On February 3rd, with my constant pleas for help, the community finally connected us to the quarantine point, where my father could go first and then have his nucleic acid tested. On the night of the 3rd, my father was sent to the only quarantine point in Hongshan District at the Hongshan District District Party School on the Third Baisha Road, which the Community said had been rushed. Before we went, the community assured us repeatedly that it was not serious, that it could not be a very dangerous patient, because there were no doctors in the quarantine, and they were too scared to deal with the serious patients.

My Dad had his first nucleic acid test on Feb. 4, the day he stopped having a fever, and my husband took the medicine from the hospital.

Who almost got rejected from the quarantine

My mother comforted some psychological, state also a little better, but still cough, sometimes out of breath. My mother had a heart attack, had a heart ablation, and had mild atrial fibrillation, so the focus of attention for a few days became my mother.

My home thermometer was taken to the quarantine point by my father, February 7 afternoon when I was packing things found a thermometer, let my mother take a temperature. She doesn't feel anything, but it's 100 degrees.

We all felt bad. My mother rarely had a cold or a fever, and the sudden onset of the fever made us realize that maybe my mother was infected, too.

I was the only one left to take care of my two young children. My Mom said she'd better go into quarantine, too, for me and the baby, because the virus is so contagious.

So I started asking the community, the street, even the People's Daily for help. Street officials told me that my mother did not even have a blood test or a CT report. It was difficult to arrange quarantine points, at least for suspected patients, but the community could not help me to send my mother to the hospital for examination.

Those days I had to cook for four people every day, do various cleaning and disinfection work, and try to coax the two daughters to stay in the room as far as possible not to go to the living room, and at night I worried that my mother would have difficulty breathing and sleeping well alone in the room, i feel very tired.

On February 8, my mother went to the hospital for a CT scan, which revealed a double lung infection.

The community kind of took care of us, sent my mom to Dad's quarantine. Before moving in, the mother asked the Quarantine Point Staff: "If there is breathing difficulties to whom to seek help? " This question, the staff scared, almost do not accept her. Because they don't have a paramedic to keep them safe. It was late at night, my mother's car dropped her off and left. My mother dragged her tired body to the community for help. It was after 2 o'clock at night before she was finally admitted.

February 9, Mother said the quarantine point issued Chinese medicine, they began to drink Chinese medicine in the evening. My Dad had two nucleic acid tests, the first negative, the second positive, and my mom's cough was getting worse.

The next afternoon, dad had a fever again. Originally, there had been no fever for four or five days. Moreover, his fever this time was only 38 degrees. My mother also had a fever of around 38 degrees every day until the afternoon. In addition, she had a bad cough. There was no medical staff to inquire at the isolation point. Her Spirit was getting worse and worse, worried about herself and worried about dad, she was on the verge of a breakdown.

Mom and dad are in a shelter hospital

On February 11, mom and dad still had a fever. MOM was so desperate to get into the hospital, it seemed like she could only be saved if she saw a doctor. I contacted the community, the street, they all said that nucleic acid results can be based on the next arrangements, and announced the Hongshan district phone is simply not connected. That night, I posted the information for help on the Internet. A volunteer added me and asked me about my parents. He said that he would help me report that there might be hope for a bed. I was still explaining the situation to the volunteers in the middle of the night, but maybe it was because my parents didn't have the serious underlying diseases of hypertension and coronary heart disease, or the breathing difficulties and lack of oxygen, so even the reports were at the bottom of the list.

In addition to taking care of the children and doing routine disinfection, I was also under a lot of pressure, for fear of what happened to my parents, and I can not help.

On February 12th, mom and dad both tested positive for nucleic acid, which is probably a good thing. The policy for the day had become "collect what you can" and all confirmed patients would be treated accordingly.

That day, my parents were notified by the quarantine point that they would be transferred, but no one knew where. At first my mother heard that go to the shelter hospital nobody, no medicine, the conditions are very bad, so very resist to go to the shelter hospital. After our persuasion, mom finally calmed down and accepted the fact that she might go to the shelter hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Shelter Hospital for Ye's parents

At 9 pm, parents in Hongshan District were taken to the Wuhan Sports Center Stadium Shelter Hospital in Hanyang. On February 13, Mom and dad still had a fever in the late afternoon. In the middle of the night, the fever slowly subsided through sweating. Dad's fever was relatively high and he had to take an antipyretic several times to lower his temperature. The doctor in the shelter room said that his medicine had been taken for nearly 10 days, with too many side effects, tell him to stop taking them, tell my mom to stop taking them, too.

But my dad's still running a fever, and my mom and I are worried.

February 14, also on that day, my mother did not have a fever, appetite is better, but the cough is still severe, and cough will still wheeze. I think it was the environment in the shelter hospital that made her feel better, because there were so many patients like her there, and they could talk to each other, and the time went by a little faster, and it was much better than being alone in the Random Thoughts, the environment of the shelter hospital is indeed more suitable for the recuperation of patients.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A box lunch for a shelter hospital patient taken by Ye's parents

It snowed heavily in Wuhan on Feb. 15, and the first snow in 2020 came a little late. This Day, the father and mother have no longer a fever, the father condition is stable, the mother or cough severe, but the state of mind has been much better.

This hard, self-saving winter

My husband went to a hotel quarantine site on February 12. His first nucleic acid test at the quarantine site was negative. The day he came back was a little closer. I felt a little relieved, the heart that has been clenched has also let down a bit.

On February 17, the community was completely sealed off, do not let go, buy food has become a new problem, everyone can only be in the group everywhere group, or wait for six or seven days to come once a team of love to sell vegetables into the community, and then line up a long line to buy food. Many thanks to a few neighbors and friends for their help, let me and the children eat cabbage every day of the day can change the taste.

February 19, my mother has not had a fever for five days, but the cough is still severe, my father has not had a fever for four days, other symptoms are also good.

The husband was negative for both nucleic acid tests, and basically had no symptoms, but the isolation point didn't mean to bring him back.

My mom was worried they'd put me in quarantine, too, and the kids would be left alone. The community contacted me many times, saying that I should also go to the quarantine point, but I stressed to them again and again my actual situation, I do not have any discomfort, the two children are well, and need to be taken care of, so they didn't force me to go.

Today, we went to the quarantine point. Thankfully, the people on the street saw I was in difficulty and applied for the three of us to be moved to a hotel to be quarantined.
